      <h3 class="card-title" style="font-size:14px;">🕐 Fun Clock Facts</h3>
      <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(200px,1fr));gap:12px;margin-top:8px;">
        <div style="background:rgba(0,0,0,0.2);border-radius:10px;padding:12px;">
          <div style="font-size:12px;font-weight:700;color:var(--accent);margin-bottom:6px;">Why do clocks go clockwise?</div>
          <div style="font-size:12px;color:var(--text2);line-height:1.6;">Sundials in the northern hemisphere cast shadows moving left-to-right. When mechanical clocks were invented, they mimicked this direction — and it stuck.</div>
        </div>
        <div style="background:rgba(0,0,0,0.2);border-radius:10px;padding:12px;">
          <div style="font-size:12px;font-weight:700;color:var(--accent);margin-bottom:6px;">Most accurate clock</div>
          <div style="font-size:12px;color:var(--text2);line-height:1.6;">Optical atomic clocks are accurate to within 1 second every 15 billion years — longer than the age of the universe.</div>
        </div>
        <div style="background:rgba(0,0,0,0.2);border-radius:10px;padding:12px;">
          <div style="font-size:12px;font-weight:700;color:var(--accent);margin-bottom:6px;">UTC — The world's time standard</div>
          <div style="font-size:12px;color:var(--text2);line-height:1.6;">Coordinated Universal Time (UTC) is the basis for all civil time worldwide. Your device syncs to it automatically via NTP servers.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div style="max-width:900px;margin:0 auto;padding:0 24px 40px;">
    <div class="card">
