      <div style="background:rgba(0,0,0,0.2);border-radius:8px;padding:10px;text-align:center;"><div style="font-size:15px;font-weight:800;color:var(--accent);font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;">UTC+0</div><div style="font-size:11px;color:var(--text2);margin-top:3px;">London (GMT)</div></div>
      <div style="background:rgba(0,0,0,0.2);border-radius:8px;padding:10px;text-align:center;"><div style="font-size:15px;font-weight:800;color:var(--accent);font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;">UTC+1</div><div style="font-size:11px;color:var(--text2);margin-top:3px;">Paris / Berlin</div></div>
      <div style="background:rgba(0,0,0,0.2);border-radius:8px;padding:10px;text-align:center;"><div style="font-size:15px;font-weight:800;color:var(--accent);font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;">UTC+3</div><div style="font-size:11px;color:var(--text2);margin-top:3px;">Istanbul / Moscow</div></div>
      <div style="background:rgba(0,0,0,0.2);border-radius:8px;padding:10px;text-align:center;"><div style="font-size:15px;font-weight:800;color:var(--accent);font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;">UTC+5:30</div><div style="font-size:11px;color:var(--text2);margin-top:3px;">Mumbai (IST)</div></div>
      <div style="background:rgba(0,0,0,0.2);border-radius:8px;padding:10px;text-align:center;"><div style="font-size:15px;font-weight:800;color:var(--accent);font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;">UTC+8</div><div style="font-size:11px;color:var(--text2);margin-top:3px;">Beijing / Singapore</div></div>
      <div style="background:rgba(0,0,0,0.2);border-radius:8px;padding:10px;text-align:center;"><div style="font-size:15px;font-weight:800;color:var(--accent);font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;">UTC+9</div><div style="font-size:11px;color:var(--text2);margin-top:3px;">Tokyo / Seoul</div></div>
      <div style="background:rgba(0,0,0,0.2);border-radius:8px;padding:10px;text-align:center;"><div style="font-size:15px;font-weight:800;color:var(--accent);font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;">UTC+11</div><div style="font-size:11px;color:var(--text2);margin-top:3px;">Sydney (AEDT)</div></div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <h2 class="card-title">Understanding Time Zones</h2>
    <p style="color:var(--text2);font-size:14px;line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:12px;">
      Time zones are regions of the world that observe the same standard time. The world is divided into 24 main time zones, each roughly 15 degrees of longitude wide, corresponding to one hour of the Earth's 24-hour rotation. Time zones are expressed as offsets from Coordinated Universal Time (UTC), ranging from UTC−12:00 to UTC+14:00.
    </p>
    <p style="color:var(--text2);font-size:14px;line-height:1.8;">
      This table lists every standard UTC offset alongside the current local time for that zone, updated every second. Use it to convert between time zones quickly, plan international calls, or check what time it is anywhere in the world without needing to do any mental arithmetic.
    </p>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- WEEK PAGE -->
<div class="page" id="page-week">
  <h1 style="font-size:clamp(18px,4vw,28px);font-weight:800;color:var(--text);text-align:center;margin-bottom:8px;padding:40px 24px 0;">What Week Number Is It Today?</h1>
  <div class="week-big">
    <h2 class="week-label" style="margin-bottom:16px;">This Week</h2>
    <div class="week-number" id="weekNum">—</div>
    <div class="week-label">OF THE YEAR</div>
    <div style="margin-top:32px;color:var(--text2);font-size:14px;" id="weekInfo"></div>
  </div>
  <div class="card">
    <h3 class="card-title">Week Calendar for the Year</h3>
    <div id="weekCalendar" style="overflow-x:auto;"></div>
  </div>

  <!-- Info Card replacing Ad Unit 9 -->
  <div class="card" style="margin:24px 24px;background:linear-gradient(135deg,rgba(168,85,247,0.06) 0%,rgba(0,212,255,0.06) 100%);border-color:rgba(168,85,247,0.18);">
    <h3 class="card-title" style="font-size:14px;">📆 Did You Know? Week Number Facts</h3>
    <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(200px,1fr));gap:12px;margin-top:8px;">
      <div style="background:rgba(0,0,0,0.2);border-radius:10px;padding:12px;">
        <div style="font-size:12px;font-weight:700;color:var(--accent);margin-bottom:6px;">ISO 8601 Standard</div>
        <div style="font-size:12px;color:var(--text2);line-height:1.6;">Under the international ISO 8601 standard, weeks always start on Monday. Week 1 is defined as the week containing the year's first Thursday.</div>
      </div>
      <div style="background:rgba(0,0,0,0.2);border-radius:10px;padding:12px;">
        <div style="font-size:12px;font-weight:700;color:var(--accent);margin-bottom:6px;">52 or 53 Weeks?</div>
        <div style="font-size:12px;color:var(--text2);line-height:1.6;">Most years have 52 ISO weeks. A year has 53 weeks if it starts on Thursday, or if it's a leap year starting on Wednesday or Thursday.</div>
      </div>
      <div style="background:rgba(0,0,0,0.2);border-radius:10px;padding:12px;">
        <div style="font-size:12px;font-weight:700;color:var(--accent);margin-bottom:6px;">Business Use</div>
        <div style="font-size:12px;color:var(--text2);line-height:1.6;">Industries like manufacturing, finance, and logistics use week numbers instead of dates for scheduling, making global coordination much simpler.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="card" style="margin:0 24px 40px;">
    <h2 class="card-title">About Week Numbers</h2>
    <p style="color:var(--text2);font-size:14px;line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:12px;">
      Week numbers divide the year into 52 or 53 numbered weeks, which is especially useful for business planning, project scheduling, and payroll cycles. The most widely used standard is ISO 8601, where weeks start on Monday and the first week of the year is the one containing the year's first Thursday.
    </p>
    <p style="color:var(--text2);font-size:14px;line-height:1.8;">
      Week numbers are widely used in industries such as manufacturing, logistics, finance, construction, and project management because they provide a universal reference point that everyone on a team can use, regardless of the specific dates in a given month. The week calendar above shows all weeks in the current year with the current week highlighted.
    </p>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- DATE CALC PAGE -->
<div class="page" id="page-date">
  <h1 style="font-size:clamp(18px,4vw,28px);font-weight:800;color:var(--text);text-align:center;margin-bottom:8px;padding-top:40px;padding-left:24px;padding-right:24px;">Date Calculator — Days Between Two Dates</h1>
  <h2 class="section-title" style="margin-top:8px;">📅 Date Calculator</h2>
  <div class="section-sub">Calculate the difference between two dates</div>
  <div class="card">
    <h3 class="card-title">Dates</h3>
    <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:16px;margin-bottom:16px;">
      <div>
        <div class="picker-label" style="margin-bottom:8px;">Start Date</div>
        <input type="date" id="dateFrom">
      </div>
      <div>
        <div class="picker-label" style="margin-bottom:8px;">End Date</div>
        <input type="date" id="dateTo">
      </div>
    </div>
    <button class="btn btn-primary" onclick="calcDate()">Calculate</button>
    <div class="calc-result" id="dateResult">
      <h3 class="card-title">Result</h3>
      <div class="result-grid" id="dateResultGrid"></div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Info Card replacing Ad Unit 10 -->
  <div class="card" style="margin:24px 24px;background:linear-gradient(135deg,rgba(0,212,255,0.06) 0%,rgba(168,85,247,0.06) 100%);border-color:rgba(0,212,255,0.18);">
    <h3 class="card-title" style="font-size:14px;">📅 Historical Date Milestones</h3>
    <p style="color:var(--text2);font-size:13px;line-height:1.7;margin-bottom:12px;">Some famous spans of time that shaped our world — calculated in days:</p>
    <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(170px,1fr));gap:10px;">
      <div style="background:rgba(0,0,0,0.2);border-radius:10px;padding:12px;text-align:center;">
        <div style="font-size:18px;font-weight:800;color:var(--accent);font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;">~4 years</div>
        <div style="font-size:12px;color:var(--text);font-weight:600;margin-top:4px;">World War II</div>
        <div style="font-size:11px;color:var(--text2);margin-top:2px;">Sep 1939 – Sep 1945</div>
      </div>
      <div style="background:rgba(0,0,0,0.2);border-radius:10px;padding:12px;text-align:center;">
        <div style="font-size:18px;font-weight:800;color:var(--accent);font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;">8 days</div>
        <div style="font-size:12px;color:var(--text);font-weight:600;margin-top:4px;">Moon to Earth</div>
        <div style="font-size:11px;color:var(--text2);margin-top:2px;">Apollo 11 mission duration</div>
      </div>
      <div style="background:rgba(0,0,0,0.2);border-radius:10px;padding:12px;text-align:center;">
        <div style="font-size:18px;font-weight:800;color:var(--accent);font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;">100 days</div>
        <div style="font-size:12px;color:var(--text);font-weight:600;margin-top:4px;">100 Day Rule</div>
        <div style="font-size:11px;color:var(--text2);margin-top:2px;">Classic new habit benchmark</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <h2 class="card-title">About the Date Calculator</h2>
    <p style="color:var(--text2);font-size:14px;line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:12px;">
      This free date calculator instantly shows the difference between two dates in days, weeks, months, years, hours, and minutes. Simply enter a start date and an end date, then press Calculate to see the full breakdown. The calculator handles any date range — past or future — with no limit.
    </p>
    <p style="color:var(--text2);font-size:14px;line-height:1.8;">
      Date calculators are useful for many real-world applications: finding out how many days until a deadline, how long ago an event occurred, how many days are between two appointments, or planning a project schedule with specific milestones.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <h2 class="card-title">Common Uses for a Date Calculator</h2>
    <ul style="color:var(--text2);font-size:14px;line-height:2;padding-left:20px;">
      <li><strong style="color:var(--text);">Project deadlines</strong> — Find out exactly how many days you have to complete a project or assignment.</li>
      <li><strong style="color:var(--text);">Pregnancy tracking</strong> — Calculate how many weeks along a pregnancy is, or how many days until the estimated due date.</li>
      <li><strong style="color:var(--text);">Legal &amp; financial</strong> — Determine the number of days between contract dates, payment due dates, or court deadlines.</li>
      <li><strong style="color:var(--text);">Anniversaries &amp; milestones</strong> — See how many days have passed since your wedding, graduation, or first day at a job.</li>
      <li><strong style="color:var(--text);">Travel planning</strong> — Count the exact number of days in a trip for visa applications, hotel bookings, or itinerary planning.</li>
      <li><strong style="color:var(--text);">Health &amp; fitness</strong> — Track how many days into a workout program, diet, or recovery period you are.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- HOURS CALC PAGE -->
<div class="page" id="page-hours">
  <h1 style="font-size:clamp(18px,4vw,28px);font-weight:800;color:var(--text);text-align:center;margin-bottom:8px;padding-top:40px;padding-left:24px;padding-right:24px;">Hour Calculator — Total Working Hours</h1>
  <h2 class="section-title" style="margin-top:8px;">⏱ Hour Calculator</h2>
  <div class="section-sub">Calculate working hours and time differences</div>
  <div class="card">
    <h3 class="card-title">Time Ranges</h3>
    <div class="hours-rows" id="hoursRows">
      <div class="hours-row">
        <input type="time" class="start-time">
        <input type="time" class="end-time">
        <button class="btn-icon" onclick="removeHoursRow(this)">✕</button>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div style="display:flex;gap:10px;margin-bottom:16px;">
      <button class="btn btn-secondary" onclick="addHoursRow()">+ Add Row</button>
    </div>
    <button class="btn btn-primary" onclick="calcHours()">Calculate</button>
    <div class="calc-result" id="hoursResult">
      <h3 class="card-title">Total Duration</h3>
      <div id="hoursResultText" style="font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:32px;color:var(--accent);margin-top:12px;"></div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Info Card replacing Ad Unit 11 -->
  <div class="card" style="margin:24px 24px;background:linear-gradient(135deg,rgba(168,85,247,0.06) 0%,rgba(0,212,255,0.06) 100%);border-color:rgba(168,85,247,0.18);">
    <h3 class="card-title" style="font-size:14px;">⏱ Hours in Perspective</h3>
    <p style="color:var(--text2);font-size:13px;line-height:1.7;margin-bottom:12px;">How long does it really take to become an expert? Some well-known time benchmarks:</p>
    <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(160px,1fr));gap:10px;">
      <div style="background:rgba(0,0,0,0.2);border-radius:10px;padding:12px;text-align:center;">
        <div style="font-size:22px;font-weight:800;color:var(--accent);font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;">20 hrs</div>
        <div style="font-size:12px;color:var(--text);font-weight:600;margin-top:4px;">Learn Any Skill</div>
        <div style="font-size:11px;color:var(--text2);margin-top:2px;">Josh Kaufman's "First 20 Hours" rule</div>
      </div>
      <div style="background:rgba(0,0,0,0.2);border-radius:10px;padding:12px;text-align:center;">
        <div style="font-size:22px;font-weight:800;color:var(--accent);font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;">10,000 hrs</div>
        <div style="font-size:12px;color:var(--text);font-weight:600;margin-top:4px;">Mastery</div>
        <div style="font-size:11px;color:var(--text2);margin-top:2px;">Malcolm Gladwell's popular theory</div>
      </div>
      <div style="background:rgba(0,0,0,0.2);border-radius:10px;padding:12px;text-align:center;">
        <div style="font-size:22px;font-weight:800;color:var(--accent);font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;">2,000 hrs</div>
        <div style="font-size:12px;color:var(--text);font-weight:600;margin-top:4px;">Work Year</div>
        <div style="font-size:11px;color:var(--text2);margin-top:2px;">Average full-time employee per year</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <h2 class="card-title">About the Hour Calculator</h2>
    <p style="color:var(--text2);font-size:14px;line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:12px;">
      This hour calculator adds up multiple time ranges and gives you the total number of hours and minutes worked or elapsed. Enter one or more start-time and end-time pairs — for example, your morning shift from 09:00 to 12:30 and your afternoon shift from 13:30 to 17:00 — and the calculator instantly totals the duration.
    </p>
    <p style="color:var(--text2);font-size:14px;line-height:1.8;">
      Overnight ranges are supported automatically, so if your shift starts at 22:00 and ends at 06:00, the calculator correctly computes 8 hours rather than a negative value. Add as many rows as you need for complex multi-shift days.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <h2 class="card-title">Who Uses an Hour Calculator?</h2>
    <ul style="color:var(--text2);font-size:14px;line-height:2;padding-left:20px;">
      <li><strong style="color:var(--text);">Freelancers &amp; contractors</strong> — Calculate billable hours accurately for client invoices.</li>
      <li><strong style="color:var(--text);">Employees</strong> — Verify your total worked hours against a timesheet before submitting payroll.</li>
      <li><strong style="color:var(--text);">Managers &amp; HR</strong> — Quickly add up shift hours for team scheduling and payroll processing.</li>
      <li><strong style="color:var(--text);">Students</strong> — Track study hours across multiple sessions in a day or week.</li>
      <li><strong style="color:var(--text);">Athletes &amp; coaches</strong> — Total up training time across multiple practice sessions.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- AGE CALC PAGE -->
<div class="page" id="page-age">
  <h1 style="font-size:clamp(18px,4vw,28px);font-weight:800;color:var(--text);text-align:center;margin-bottom:8px;padding-top:40px;padding-left:24px;padding-right:24px;">Age Calculator — How Old Am I?</h1>
  <h2 class="section-title" style="margin-top:8px;">🎂 Age Calculator</h2>
  <div class="section-sub">Enter your date of birth to calculate your age in detail</div>
  <div class="card">
    <h3 class="card-title">Date of Birth</h3>
    <div style="margin-bottom:16px;">
      <div class="picker-label" style="margin-bottom:8px;">Date of Birth</div>
      <input type="date" id="birthDate">
    </div>
    <button class="btn btn-primary" onclick="calcAge()">Calculate</button>
    <div class="calc-result" id="ageResult">
      <h3 class="card-title">Age Details</h3>
      <div class="result-grid" id="ageResultGrid"></div>
      <div id="ageExtra" style="margin-top:16px;color:var(--text2);font-size:14px;line-height:1.8;"></div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Info Card replacing Ad Unit 12 -->
  <div class="card" style="margin:24px 24px;background:linear-gradient(135deg,rgba(0,212,255,0.06) 0%,rgba(168,85,247,0.06) 100%);border-color:rgba(0,212,255,0.18);">
    <h3 class="card-title" style="font-size:14px;">🎂 Age Around the World</h3>
    <p style="color:var(--text2);font-size:13px;line-height:1.7;margin-bottom:12px;">Different cultures count and celebrate age in fascinating ways:</p>
    <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(190px,1fr));gap:10px;">
      <div style="background:rgba(0,0,0,0.2);border-radius:10px;padding:12px;">
        <div style="font-size:12px;font-weight:700;color:var(--accent);margin-bottom:5px;">🇰🇷 South Korea</div>
        <div style="font-size:12px;color:var(--text2);line-height:1.6;">Traditionally, Koreans count age from 1 at birth and add a year each January 1st — so a baby born in December is "2" by New Year.</div>
      </div>
      <div style="background:rgba(0,0,0,0.2);border-radius:10px;padding:12px;">
        <div style="font-size:12px;font-weight:700;color:var(--accent);margin-bottom:5px;">🎉 Leap Year Birthdays</div>
        <div style="font-size:12px;color:var(--text2);line-height:1.6;">People born on February 29 only get a "real" birthday every 4 years. They're called "leaplings" and make up about 0.07% of the world's population.</div>
      </div>
      <div style="background:rgba(0,0,0,0.2);border-radius:10px;padding:12px;">
        <div style="font-size:12px;font-weight:700;color:var(--accent);margin-bottom:5px;">🧬 Oldest Verified Person</div>
        <div style="font-size:12px;color:var(--text2);line-height:1.6;">Jeanne Calment of France lived to 122 years and 164 days — the oldest verified human age ever recorded, born in 1875.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <h2 class="card-title">About the Age Calculator</h2>
    <p style="color:var(--text2);font-size:14px;line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:12px;">
      This free age calculator tells you exactly how old you are in years, months, and days — plus total days, total weeks, total hours, and the number of minutes you've been alive. It also shows how many days remain until your next birthday.
    </p>
    <p style="color:var(--text2);font-size:14px;line-height:1.8;">
      Enter your date of birth and press Calculate. The result updates instantly and is calculated based on today's date. The age calculator correctly handles leap years and variable month lengths, so the result is always precise down to the day.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <h2 class="card-title">Interesting Age Facts</h2>
    <p style="color:var(--text2);font-size:14px;line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:12px;">
      Most people know their age in years, but here are some surprising ways to think about how old you are:
    </p>
    <ul style="color:var(--text2);font-size:14px;line-height:2;padding-left:20px;">
      <li>A 30-year-old has lived approximately <strong style="color:var(--text);">10,950 days</strong> and over <strong style="color:var(--text);">262,000 hours</strong>.</li>
      <li>By age 18, you've experienced about <strong style="color:var(--text);">4–5 leap years</strong>, adding extra days to your life count.</li>
      <li>People born on February 29 only have a "real" birthday every 4 years, making them technically much younger by birthday count.</li>
      <li>The age at which most people are considered legally adult varies by country — from 15 in some nations to 21 in others.</li>
      <li>In some East Asian cultures, a person is considered 1 year old at birth, making everyone "older" by one year compared to Western age counting.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- ALARM RING MODAL -->
<div class="modal-overlay" id="alarmModal">
  <div class="modal-box">
    <div class="modal-icon">⏰</div>
    <div class="modal-title">ALARM!</div>
    <div class="modal-time" id="modalTime">00:00</div>
    <div class="modal-name" id="modalName">Your alarm is ringing</div>
    <div class="modal-btns">
      <button class="btn btn-danger" onclick="stopAlarm()">■ Stop</button>
      <button class="btn btn-secondary" onclick="snoozeAlarm()">💤 Snooze</button>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- SETTINGS MODAL -->
<div class="settings-modal" id="settingsModal">
  <div class="settings-box">
    <div style="display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center;margin-bottom:24px;">
      <div style="font-size:18px;font-weight:800;">⚙️ Settings</div>
      <button class="btn-icon" onclick="document.getElementById('settingsModal').classList.remove('visible')">✕</button>
    </div>
    <div class="settings-row">
      <div><div class="settings-label">Repeat alarm</div><div class="settings-desc">Keeps ringing until dismissed</div></div>
      <div class="toggle on" id="toggleRepeat" onclick="this.classList.toggle('on')"></div>
    </div>
    <div class="settings-row">
      <div><div class="settings-label">Show alarm time</div></div>
      <div class="toggle on" id="toggleShowTime" onclick="this.classList.toggle('on')"></div>
    </div>
    <div class="settings-row">
      <div><div class="settings-label">Show progress bar</div></div>
      <div class="toggle on" id="toggleProgress" onclick="this.classList.toggle('on')"></div>
    </div>
    <div class="settings-row" style="flex-direction:column;align-items:flex-start;gap:12px;">
      <div class="settings-label">Snooze duration: <span id="snoozeVal">10</span> min</div>
      <div style="display:flex;gap:8px;flex-wrap:wrap;">
        <button class="quick-btn" onclick="setSnooze(1)">1</button>
        <button class="quick-btn" onclick="setSnooze(5)">5</button>
        <button class="quick-btn" onclick="setSnooze(10)">10</button>
        <button class="quick-btn" onclick="setSnooze(15)">15</button>
        <button class="quick-btn" onclick="setSnooze(30)">30</button>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="settings-row" style="flex-direction:column;align-items:flex-start;gap:12px;">
      <div class="settings-label">Volume: <span id="volVal">100</span>%</div>
      <input type="range" id="volSlider" min="0" max="100" value="100" oninput="document.getElementById('volVal').textContent=this.value">
    </div>
    <button class="btn btn-secondary" style="margin-top:16px;width:100%;" onclick="document.getElementById('settingsModal').classList.remove('visible')">Close</button>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- ABOUT PAGE -->
<div class="page" id="page-about">
  <script type="application/ld+json">
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "AboutPage",
